fcam (1.1.1-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * 1296x968 RAW now works (648x492 still doesn't).

  * dcraw and derived libraries can now find our thumbnails

  * The settings of the last shot are left as the V4L2 device state on exit now, to allow other V4L2 devices to piggyback on our settings.

 -- Andrew Adams <abadams@stanford.edu>  Wed, 23 Sep 2010 18:43:00 -0700

fcam (1.1.0-2) unstable; urgency=low

  * Removed unneeded files from package

 -- Eino-Ville Talvala <talvala@stanford.edu>  Mon, 16 Aug 2010 15:20:00 -0700

fcam (1.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Numerous DNG updates and fixes: Now works with dcraw, color rendition improved in general, ACR 2010 denoising works.

  * Compatibility with N900 built-in camera night mode and BlessN900.

  * Added memory-mapped Image support

  * API break: Improved WB handling: Shots can now contain a custom WB matrix instead of just a color temperature.

  * Correct date->month conversion.

  * Various error checking improvements throughout the codebase.

 -- Eino-Ville Talvala <talvala@stanford.edu>  Mon, 16 Aug 2010 13:30:00 -0700

